<Section>
	<rubric:Rubric>
		<text:Title>
			The Problem of Induction
		</text:Title>
	</rubric:Rubric>

	<text:Paragraph>
		Hume's argument against inductive reasoning remains one of the most
		persistent challenges in epistemology. The core difficulty is that any
		justification for induction must itself rely on inductive reasoning,
		creating an unavoidable circularity.
	</text:Paragraph>
</Section>
